41c2a7b0b7ae"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Due to the presence of one two-body and two-one-body interaction vertices, \
the number of distinct fully-contracted terms of ",
 StyleBox["12 ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " second quantization operators at second order corresponds to 11",
 StyleBox["!! = 10,395",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". The results of the generation process hold identically for all the 4 \
Nambu components of the one-body potential and are the same for each of the ",
 StyleBox["16",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " Nambu components of Gorkov\[CloseCurlyQuote]s polarization propagator.  A \
significant part of these Wick\[CloseCurlyQuote]s-theorem contributions has \
to be discarded, since it corresponds either to disconnected diagrams or to \
exchange diagrams that are cancelled by the subtractive term of the \
polarization propagator.  At third order, conjoint diagrams containing one \
two-body and two one-body interaction vertices exist. Additionally, since the \
one-body potential is not invariant under permutation of the two indices, the \
filtration process accounts only for inter-vertex transpositions of \
single-particle indices."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.874645469364807*^9, 3.874645558141898*^9}, {
