   3.913874702705942*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f4ac8a67-2e32-4922-8462-\
647a1d15a817"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Filtration of the conjoint composite fully-contracted terms with one \
two-body and two identical one-body vertices. At third order, transpositions \
between single particles of both different vertices (external permutations) \
and the same vertex (internal permutations) are possible. Fully-contracted \
terms which are mapped one another by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q, r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are identified and summed, eventually canceling out the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"ae7b4d5e-65d3-4b24-9765-e6fb4c6d2cd8"],
 " factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "pqrs"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "97250388-0c59-42cc-bd30-85d6540709c4"],
 " interaction vertex. The procedure is repeated 2 times, assuming in the \
second case, a permutation of the indices of the two identical one-body \
vertices. The latter consists of two transpositions of single-particle \
indices, ",
 StyleBox["e \[RightTeeArrow] g",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["f \[RightTeeArrow] h. ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "As a result, 240 third-order conjoint composite fully-contracted terms of \
this kind are found."
}], "Text",
