Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Diagonally-dressed disjoint Bogoliubov diagrams with two identical one-body \
vertices\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.874644843789677*^9, 3.8746448545752873`*^9}, {
   3.883112065177337*^9, 3.883112118360941*^9}, {3.8831146011227875`*^9, 
   3.8831146201744213`*^9}, {3.883115184479356*^9, 3.8831151965813236`*^9}, {
   3.8884058729915524`*^9, 3.8884058731821747`*^9}, {3.892800153537215*^9, 
   3.8928001610648518`*^9}, {3.897041751372193*^9, 3.8970417738128204`*^9}, {
   3.8970432846114845`*^9, 3.897043286022911*^9}, 3.911883818478182*^9, {
   3.9138746160355434`*^9, 3.9138746229199734`*^9}, {3.9138747008118477`*^9, 
   3.913874702705942*^9}, {3.9139775702698774`*^9, 3.9139775768964944`*^9}, {
   3.914042108780902*^9, 3.9140421190594597`*^9}, 
   3.914044189694788*^9},ExpressionUUID->"36daff87-2ef3-4a7f-b500-\
4c91df238772"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Filtration of the diagonally-dressed disjoint Bogoliubov fully-contracted \
terms with one two-body and two identical one-body vertices. At third order, \
transpositions between single particles of both different vertices (external \
permutations) and the same vertex (internal permutations) are possible. \
Fully-contracted terms which are mapped one another by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q, r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are identified and summed, eventually canceling out the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"c16ca475-19fa-4df1-b042-e582ca9d0e12"],
 " factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "pqrs"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6fb4e704-ec14-400e-ac1d-8e30f79a2472"],
 " interaction vertex. The procedure is repeated 2 times, assuming in the \
second case, a permutation of the indices of the two identical one-body \
vertices. The latter consists of two transpositions of single-particle \
indices, ",
 StyleBox["e \[RightTeeArrow] g",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["f \[RightTeeArrow] h. ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "As a result, 86 third-order diagonally-dressed disjoint Bogoliubov \
fully-contracted terms of this kind are found."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8836806708732624`*^9, 3.883680671103075*^9}, {
   3.8836807100445924`*^9, 3.8836809748029747`*^9}, {3.88368106035993*^9, 
   3.88368123630155*^9}, {3.8884066008391533`*^9, 3.8884066027299986`*^9}, {
