Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Diagonally-and-antidiagonally-dressed disjoint Bogoliubov diagrams with \
non-identical one-body vertices\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.874644843789677*^9, 3.8746448545752873`*^9}, {
   3.883112065177337*^9, 3.883112118360941*^9}, {3.8831146011227875`*^9, 
   3.8831146201744213`*^9}, {3.883115184479356*^9, 3.8831151965813236`*^9}, {
   3.8884058729915524`*^9, 3.8884058731821747`*^9}, {3.892800153537215*^9, 
   3.8928001610648518`*^9}, {3.897041751372193*^9, 3.8970417738128204`*^9}, {
   3.8970432846114845`*^9, 3.897043286022911*^9}, 3.911883818478182*^9, {
   3.9138746160355434`*^9, 3.9138746229199734`*^9}, {3.9139762832276554`*^9, 
   3.913976295461795*^9}, {3.9140422900962625`*^9, 3.9140423009929795`*^9}, 
   3.9140439590709305`*^9, {3.9140455925433073`*^9, 
   3.9140456027003417`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"eb5d94a0-d48b-4b42-bef2-\
93c9047078de"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Filtration of the diagonally-and-antidiagonally-dressed disjoint Bogoliubov \
diagrams with non-identical one-body vertices. At third order, the \
transpositions between single-particle indices of different two-body vertices \
(external permutations) are not possible and the overall corresponding \
combinatorial factor is ",
 StyleBox["1!",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". On the other hand, transposition between single-particle index of the \
same two-body vertex are available. Fully-contracted terms which are mapped \
one another by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are identified and summed, eventually canceling out the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e4ca6997-d11d-4bd5-a62e-536b249bc40f"],
 " at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "pqrs"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c6bbf2dc-f7dd-4bf6-b1bd-d283eaee4baf"],
 " interaction vertex. The cancellation is only partial when one-body \
propagators linking a vertex to itself are present, although such topologies \
do not appear in third-order conjoint composite diagrams with two one-body \
vertices. Transpositions internal to the one-body vertices are not allowed, \
as well as exchanges between one-body vertices of different kind."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->CompressedData["
1:eJxTTMoPSmViYGAQAWIQfeTj7eKO928cU3weg2nf3IMVIPrHxpszQXRPS/cS
EO2zrHMXiI64JcXZ8+ONo1pMOJg+5PqsduOvN47zyvnrQPQOBr7cINW3jn2V
