7c24e36ba0f5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Filtration of the disconnected fully-contracted terms with one two-body and \
two identical one-body vertices. At third order, transpositions between \
single particles of both different vertices (external permutations) and the \
same vertex (internal permutations) are possible. Fully-contracted terms \
which are mapped one another by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q, r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are identified and summed, eventually canceling out the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"7be69902-8736-4cdb-9d34-fe92ce004e97"],
 " factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "pqrs"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7e566655-a397-4329-8257-bfcc4c3828b3"],
 " interaction vertex. The procedure is repeated 2 times, assuming in the \
second case, a permutation of the indices of the two identical one-body \
vertices. The latter consists of two transpositions of single-particle \
indices, ",
 StyleBox["e \[RightTeeArrow] g",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["f \[RightTeeArrow] h. ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "As a result, 534 third-order disconnected fully-contracted terms of this \
kind are found."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8836806708732624`*^9, 3.883680671103075*^9}, {
   3.8836807100445924`*^9, 3.8836809748029747`*^9}, {3.88368106035993*^9, 
